org.hibernate.query.criteria.sqm

Class JpaParameterSqmWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.query.criteria.sqm.JpaParameterSqmWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InferableTypeSqmExpression, SqmExpression, SqmParameter, SqmSelectableNode, SqmNode, SqmTypedNode, SqmVisitableNode

    public class JpaParameterSqmWrapper
extends Object
implements SqmParameter
    Wraps a JPA criteria parameter as a SQM parameter. The exact parameter instance is used to set values, so we need to use the exact instance in the Query we ultimately build
    See Also:

      • allowMultiValuedBinding

        public boolean allowMultiValuedBinding()
        Description copied from interface: SqmParameter
        Can a collection/array of values be bound to this parameter?

        This is allowed in very limited contexts within the query:

        1. as the value of an IN predicate if the only value is a single param
        2. (in non-strict JPA mode) as the final vararg to a function
        Specified by:
        allowMultiValuedBinding in interface SqmParameter
        Returns:
        true if binding collection/array of values is allowed for this parameter; false otherwise.
